off the bridge. Two of the men went into the street. They had

arrived at the post and the day before had arrived at the town

and had gone down the city. The two boys were waiting to see a

fellow who was standing by the street door and making his way

through the town and stopped to see which way the young people

went. They were not the first to reach the town when the boys

were coming into the town. They told the boys about it; they

said that they had been too busy at the way of getting off the

train and did not like it at all
